          "username": "HongHuiXiao"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-10-12 03:45:45.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nSorry for long delay since last comment, if I understand correctly, this patch will act as VESagent in the DACE framework, right?\n\nIt looks like there is only information collection in this patch. So,\n\n1. how will this VESagent send data to VEScollector?\n2. is there any interaction between this VESagent and DMaap? Or the agent here will leave that to the VEScollector in DCAE?\n3. Is there any consideration about event handler? Will it be in the VESagent or other places?\n\nSorry if above questions are stupid :)",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "20f9d5b0d9853d57d197e26485b8b98d508233b2",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1331,
          "name": "Arun Arora",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "arunarora.dev@gmail.com",
          "username": "arun_arora"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2017-10-12 04:35:39.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nThis patch will act as VESagent in the DACE framework, right?\n[Arun] The VESAgent in this patch is part of multicloud module which will interact with VESCollector (inside DCAE) to give FCAPS info to VESColloctor\n\nIt looks like there is only information collection in this patch. \n[Arun] Information collection and sending to VESCollector\n\n1. how will this VESagent send data to VEScollector?\n[Arun] VESAgent collects the information about bad VMs and sends info in HTTP req to VESCollector's IP and port. IP and port are stored in Agent.properties file. The payload is JSON file\n\n2. is there any interaction between this VESagent and DMaap? Or the agent here will leave that to the VEScollector in DCAE?\n[Arun] No direct interaction between VESagent and DMaap.\n\n3. Is there any consideration about event handler? Will it be in the VESagent or other places?\n[Arun] For now the mechanism is to poll for VMs and collect the info about bad VMs. Then send the info to VESCollector. This mechanism is inside VESAgent.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "3e109b8bd0d6caad09fd745ec8fa408d071eb73e",
